case_address_found_1: Upper Falls intake at the Howard Street Bride on the Spokane River at Riverfront Park
case_circumstances: The body was found by an employee who was checking the intake boom near the Howard Street Bridge. The worker spotted the human remains snagged underneath and called law enforcement. The body was in an advanced state of decomposition. The body showed the presence of severe calcific atherosclerosis with high grade obstruction of the lumen. Sections of the aorta also show severe calfific atherosclerosis. Dental information was submitted to the Washington State Patrol but no possible comparisons were made. A mitochondrail DNA sequence was obtained through samples sent to the FBI Laboratory in 2004. The same lab is working on a possible nuclear DNA sample from tissue blocks submitted in July of 2008.
